Foreign Whispers

Foreign Whispers is an end-to-end dubbing pipeline that takes an input video, transcribes the speech, translates it into a target language, aligns the translated text with the original timing, and generates a synchronized dubbed output.

The system is designed as a fully functional, reproducible application that can be deployed locally using Docker and accessed through a browser interface.



Project Overview

This application performs a complete speech-to-speech pipeline:

- Transcribes speech from an input video
- Translates text into a target language
- Aligns translated segments with original timing
- Applies timing corrections using cumulative drift
- Generates speech using text-to-speech (TTS)
- Produces a final dubbed output video

The frontend allows users to run the pipeline and view results directly in the browser.



System Architecture

The project is organized into the following components:

Backend (`api/`)
- Handles all processing logic
- Exposes API endpoints for the pipeline
- Coordinates transcription, translation, alignment, and TTS

Core Pipeline (`foreign_whispers/`)
- Alignment logic (timing + drift correction)
- Speaker diarization
- Evaluation metrics and scorecard
- Voice resolution for speaker-based TTS

Frontend (`frontend/`)
- Browser interface for selecting videos
- Triggers the pipeline
- Displays results



Key Features

- End-to-end speech translation pipeline
- Timing-aware alignment with cumulative drift correction
- Segment-level processing for flexibility
- Evaluation scorecard for alignment quality
- gTTS-based speech generation (stable)
- Optional per-speaker TTS using Chatterbox
- Docker-based reproducible deployment



Text-to-Speech Design

The system uses **gTTS** as the primary TTS method because it is stable and reliable.

An advanced **Chatterbox-based per-speaker TTS system** was implemented to support voice selection based on speaker labels. However, since it depends on external services and voice files, it is used as an optional feature.

If speaker-based TTS is unavailable, the system automatically falls back to gTTS to ensure consistent output.



Alignment and Evaluation

The alignment module compares original segment timing with predicted translated speech timing.

It computes:
- Duration error
- Stretch factor
- Gap shifts
- Cumulative drift

A global alignment step ensures timing adjustments are propagated across segments.

An evaluation scorecard reports:
- Mean duration error
- Severe stretch percentage
- Gap shifts
- Translation retries
- Total drift
- Overall quality score



Limitations

Some repeated words or short phrases may appear in the translated output. This occurs because the pipeline processes speech in segments, and adjacent segments may contain overlapping content.

Minor timing mismatches may also occur when translated speech differs significantly from the original duration.

These limitations are common in segment-based speech translation systems.



How to Run the Application

1. Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/sarahchamounn/foreign-whispers.git
cd foreign-whispers

2. Create Environment File

cp .env.example .env <bash>
FW_HF_TOKEN=your_token_here <bash>

3. Start the Application
<bash> docker compose --profile cpu down
docker compose --profile cpu up --build -d

You should see:

frontend (port 8501)
backend API (port 8080)
TTS service (port 8020)


Frontend - http://localhost:8501
Backend API - http://localhost:8080
Chatterbox TTS - http://localhost:8020

6. View Logs (if needed)
<bash> docker compose --profile cpu logs -f

Screen Recording:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Scyq-rlLNYQ 

Sample Input Video:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uOX2Qp16FfY&t=9s

Sample Output Video:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QqMAU0FMfl4

This project demonstrates a complete and reproducible AI pipeline that integrates transcription, translation, alignment, and speech generation into a single system.

The pipeline prioritizes stability using gTTS while supporting advanced features such as speaker-based voice selection for future improvements.
